---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { t } from '../../i18n/translations';
import { withBase } from '../../i18n/utils';

const locale = 'en';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Research Question"
  description="The central research question: How is political legitimacy reconstructed in the discourse of HTS / Ahmad al-Sharaa between 2011 and 2025?"
  locale={locale}
>

<section class="section rq-hero">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="page-kicker">Research design</span>
    <h1 class="page-title">Research Question</h1>
    <p class="page-subtitle">Central question and analytical framework</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container rq-body">

    <div class="rq-main">

      <div class="rq-block">
        <h2 class="rq-block__title">Central Research Question</h2>
        <blockquote class="rq-quote">
          How is political legitimacy reconstructed in the discourse of
          Hayʾat Taḥrīr al-Shām / Ahmad al-Sharaa between 2011 and 2025,
          and what role do concepts such as
          <span lang="ar" dir="rtl">الدولة</span> (state),
          <span lang="ar" dir="rtl">الأمن</span> (security),
          <span lang="ar" dir="rtl">المواطنة</span> (citizenship),
          <span lang="ar" dir="rtl">الدولة المدنية</span> (civil state), and
          <span lang="ar" dir="rtl">الاعتراف الدولي</span> (international recognition) play?
        </blockquote>
      </div>

      <div class="rq-block">
        <h2 class="rq-block__title">Sub-questions</h2>
        <ol class="rq-list">
          <li>What linguistic and discursive strategies does Ahmad al-Sharaa use to legitimise the transition from an armed faction to a governing authority?</li>
          <li>How do legitimation strategies (following van Leeuwen: authorisation, moral evaluation, rationalisation, narrative) change across the four analytical phases?</li>
          <li>Which key terms — particularly Islamic, statist, and internationalised — become central in which phases, and how does their meaning shift?</li>
          <li>To what extent do changes in discourse reflect responses to external actors (international community, Syrian population, Islamic scholarship)?</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <div class="rq-block">
        <h2 class="rq-block__title">Theoretical Framework</h2>
        <p>
          The project combines critical discourse analysis with political conceptual history (Koselleck).
          The central analytical reference framework is Theo van Leeuwen's model of legitimation
          (<em>Discourse and Practice</em>, 2008), which distinguishes four main strategies:
        </p>
        <div class="rq-theory-grid">
          <div class="rq-theory-card">
            <h3>Authorisation</h3>
            <p>Legitimation by reference to authority — religious, political, or traditional.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rq-theory-card">
            <h3>Moral Evaluation</h3>
            <p>Legitimation by reference to a value system — religious or secular norms.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rq-theory-card">
            <h3>Rationalisation</h3>
            <p>Legitimation through utility or institutional logic — pragmatic justification.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rq-theory-card">
            <h3>Narrative / Mythopoesis</h3>
            <p>Legitimation through embedding in collective history, identity, and future vision.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p>Weber's triad of legitimate domination (traditional, charismatic, rational-legal) is used as a contextualising framework.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="rq-block">
        <h2 class="rq-block__title">Analytical Stance</h2>
        <div class="rq-method-statement">
          <p class="rq-method-statement__text">
            The project analyses legitimacy discourses and legitimation strategies.
            It does not evaluate or legitimise political actors.
            The research question is descriptive-analytical, not normative.
            All interpretations are explicitly marked as such and tied to source evidence.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <aside class="rq-sidebar">
      <div class="rq-sidebar-card">
        <p class="rq-sidebar-card__label">Key concepts</p>
        <ul class="rq-concept-list">
          <li><span lang="ar" dir="rtl">الدولة</span> — State</li>
          <li><span lang="ar" dir="rtl">الأمن</span> — Security</li>
          <li><span lang="ar" dir="rtl">المواطنة</span> — Citizenship</li>
          <li><span lang="ar" dir="rtl">الدولة المدنية</span> — Civil State</li>
          <li><span lang="ar" dir="rtl">الاعتراف الدولي</span> — International Recognition</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="rq-sidebar-card">
        <p class="rq-sidebar-card__label">Analysis period</p>
        <p class="rq-sidebar-card__val" dir="ltr">2013–2026</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rq-sidebar-card">
        <p class="rq-sidebar-card__label">Methodological framework</p>
        <ul class="rq-ref-list">
          <li>Van Leeuwen (2008)</li>
          <li>Weber — Legitimate Domination</li>
          <li>Political Discourse Analysis</li>
          <li>Conceptual History (Koselleck)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="rq-sidebar-card">
        <p class="rq-sidebar-card__label">Further reading</p>
        <a href={withBase('/en/methodology')} class="rq-sidebar-link">Methodology →</a>
        <a href={withBase('/en/corpus')} class="rq-sidebar-link">Corpus →</a>
        <a href={withBase('/en/timeline')} class="rq-sidebar-link">Timeline →</a>
      </div>
    </aside>

  </div>
</section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
.rq-hero { background: var(--clr-bg-alt); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--clr-border); padding-bottom: var(--space-2xl); }
.rq-body { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 16rem; gap: var(--space-3xl); align-items: start; }
.rq-main { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--space-3xl); }
.rq-block { padding-bottom: var(--space-2xl); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--clr-border-light); }
.rq-block:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
.rq-block__title { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 400; color: var(--clr-text); margin-bottom: var(--space-lg); }
.rq-quote { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: clamp(1rem, 2.2vw, 1.25rem); font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; color: var(--clr-text); line-height: 1.65; border-left: 4px solid var(--clr-red); padding: var(--space-lg) var(--space-xl); margin: 0; background: rgba(139,35,35,0.03); border-radius: 0 var(--radius-md) var(--radius-md) 0; }
.rq-list { font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--clr-text-mid); line-height: 1.75; padding-left: var(--space-xl); display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--space-md); margin: 0; }
.rq-block p { font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--clr-text-mid); line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: var(--space-md); }
.rq-theory-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: var(--space-md); margin-block: var(--space-lg); }
.rq-theory-card { background: var(--clr-card); border: 1px solid var(--clr-border); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: var(--space-lg); }
.rq-theory-card h3 { font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: 0.82rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--clr-olive); margin-bottom: var(--space-xs); }
.rq-theory-card p { font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--clr-text-mid); line-height: 1.55; margin: 0; }
.rq-method-statement { background: var(--clr-card); border: 1px solid var(--clr-border-light); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: var(--space-xl); }
.rq-method-statement__text { font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--clr-text-mid); line-height: 1.75; border-left: 3px solid var(--clr-olive); padding-left: var(--space-lg); margin: 0; }
.rq-sidebar { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--space-xl); position: sticky; top: calc(3.5rem + var(--space-xl)); }
.rq-sidebar-card { background: var(--clr-card); border: 1px solid var(--clr-border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: var(--space-xl); }
.rq-sidebar-card__label { font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: 0.7rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--clr-text-muted); margin-bottom: var(--space-sm); }
.rq-sidebar-card__val { font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--clr-text); font-weight: 600; }
.rq-concept-list, .rq-ref-list { font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--clr-text-mid); line-height: 1.7; padding-left: var(--space-lg); display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 4px; margin: 0; }
.rq-sidebar-link { display: block; font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--clr-olive); text-decoration: none; margin-top: var(--space-sm); }
.rq-sidebar-link:hover { color: var(--clr-red); }
@media (max-width: 900px) { .rq-body { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } .rq-sidebar { position: static; } .rq-theory-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
</style>
